description:

Hey meine M√§use, lange ist es her...DIesmal was jeder kennt und sehr einfach zu machen ist.
Ich hoffe euch gef√§llt das Rezept. Viel Spa√ü, beim nach kochen. 

Zutaten:
Kalbsschnitzel
Pflanzen√∂l oder nach Bedarf Schmalz
Paniermehl
Mehl
4 Eier
Salz, Pfeffer
Kartoffeln
Butter
Vegeta (Kr√§tersalz)
Milch

2 Gurken
Dill
Kr√§uter
Essig/√ñl


Zubereitung:

P√ºree
1 Kg Kartoffeln, sch√§len, klein schneiden und kochen.
Die fertigen Kartoffeln in einen K√ºchenmixer geben. (Wenn kein Mixer vorhanden, dann stampfen)
250 gramm Butter und 200 ml Milch dazu geben. Mit dem Kr√§utersalz w√ºrzen und cremig mixen oder stampfen.

Schnitzel
Die D√ºnnen Kalbsschnitzel ausbreiten und mit Klarsichtfolie sehr flach klopfen. Gut auf beiden Seiten mit Salz und Pfeffer w√ºrzen.

Eier in einen Teller geben und verquirrlen. Mehl in einen tiefen Teller f√ºllen und mit Salz und Pfeffer w√ºrzen. Semmelbr√∂sel in einen tiefen Teller f√ºllen. , Nacheinander die Schnitzel kurz von beiden Seiten zuerst im Mehl wenden, dann durch das Ei ziehen und mit Semmelbr√∂seln (Paniermehl) panieren und abklopfen.

F√ºr das CrunshySchnitzel Cornflakes klein stampfen.
Die selbe Reihenfolge wie beim klassischen Schnitzel, nach dem Paniermehl wieder durch das Eis ziehen und dann das Schnitzel mit den Cornflakes ummanteln.

Reichlich Butterschmalz oder √ñl in einer Pfanne erhitzen und die Schnitzel nacheinander darin von beiden Seiten goldgelb ausbacken. Schnitzel auf K√ºchenpapier abtropfen lassen.

F√ºr den Gurkensalat, G√ºrken in feine Scheiben schneiden oder raspeln, je nach Bedarf mit Dill, Essig, √ñl und Kr√§utern w√ºrzen. (Oder ein L√∂ffel Joghurt)

Fertig ;-)

Guten Apetit

Rezept Erdbeerkuchen mit Vanillecreme

F√ºr den Teig
2 Eier (KI. M)

125 g Zucker

75 ml Milch 
60 ml Sonnenblumen√∂l
125 g Mehl
1¬Ω TI Backpulver

Puddingpulver

ZUBEREITUNG
F√ºr den Teig Eier, Salz, Zucker und Vanillezucker schaumig schlagen. Milch und √ñl unterr√ºhren.

Vanillepudding vorbereiten.

Creme darauf verteilen. Erdbeeren in Scheiben schneiden, auf der Creme verteilen. Guss nach Packungsanweisung zubereiten, auf dem Kuchen verteilen, kalt stellen.

video_title: Savarin by Pastry Chef Giuseppe Deiana
description: Il Savarin √® un impasto , molto simile al bab√†, di origine francese, dove il dolce  viene bagnato in uno sciroppo creato con acqua zucchero bucce di limoni e  con un particolare liquore, il rum .Storia narra che il Savarin e il bab√† traggano origine dalle cucine del re polacco Stanislas Leszczynski che nell‚Äô800 risiedeva in Alsazia-Lorena; il re, goloso di dolci, mal tollerava quelli tipici del territorio, perch√© troppo compatti, secchi e difficili da gustare da chi, come lui, non aveva denti. Decise cos√¨ di provare a inzuppare questi dolci in un bagno di vino o sciroppo, rimanendo piacevolmente sorpreso dal risultato. Il Savarin √® oggi un dolce molto comune della pasticceria francese, spesso spennellato con marmellata di frutta o farcito con crema chantilly, panna e frutta fresca. Ovviamente, essendo una ricetta tradizionale, √® stata modificata in molti modi, creano ad esempio delle monoporzioni.

video_title: I miei bab√†
description: Il bab√† napoletano nato in Francia un dolce di pasta lievitata morbida e soffice .Una ricetta che lega Napoli, Francia e anche Polonia, perch√© a inventarla fu proprio il re polacco Stanislao Leszczy≈Ñski, in esilio nella regione francese, che decise di aggiungere uno sciroppo al rum al kugelhopf, dolce tipico da lui considerato troppo asciutto.Nel XIX secolo il gastronomo Anthelme Brillat-Savarin invent√≤ un liquore che ben si accompagnava alle macedonie di frutta. La pasticceria francese dei fratelli Julien ebbe l'idea di chiudere la macedonia in un bab√† opportunamente spennellato di confettura di albicocche: nacque cos√¨ il Bab√† Savarin.

video_title: Glacier Calving | Polarbears SHOCKED By HUGE COLLAPSE Next To Them!
description:
Symbolic moment for global warming caught on camera when a huge iceberg is breaking off a melting glacier in Svalbard, Norway while a polar bear mommy and her cub are playing in the snow right in front of it! Subscribe for more  ‚ñ∫ https://www.youtube.com/c/LicetStudios?sub_confirmation=1 

The Svalbard glaciers cover 6% of the worldwide glacier area outside of Greenland and Antarctica, and many of them have been melting rapidly since the 1980s due to global warming. It is estimated that they could raise the sea level by 1,7 cm once melted completely. This is an archive clip now released in connection with the Glasgow climate change conference. 

Glacier calving, also known as ice calving, or iceberg calving, is the breaking of ice chunks from the edge of a glacier. It is the sudden release and breaking away of a mass of ice from a glacier, iceberg, ice front, ice shelf, or crevasse. (Find out more here: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ice_calving).

video_title: Spectacular Tidal Bore Hits Indonesian Village (Part 3) & Surprises With Unexpected Power!
description:
Spectacular moment caught on camera when several meter high waves are speeding up to 130 km inland through the Kampar River in Indonesia. The phenomenon, called "Bono", is feared by the locals to sink ships, as at full tide during the rainy season the waves can reach a height of 20 feet (6 meters) and a speed of up to 40 km/h. The wave also attracts surfers who attempt to surf the tsunami-like wave, but as the river is also inhabited by crocodiles the surfers need to be escorted by rescue boats!

A tidal bore is a tidal phenomenon in which the incoming tide forms waves of water that travels upwards against the direction of a river or a bay's current. Tidal bores only occur in a few locations worldwide with a large tidal range. Some of the most famous locations for these waves are the Kampar River in Indonesia (seen in video) and the Qiantang River in China, at which the world's largest bore is reaching heights of up to 9 meters. Unfortunately several people die each year in connection with these tidal bores (also find more information about a tidal bore here: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tidal_bore).

The Bono wave is not just one, but a series of multiple waves. Although surfing the Bono waves can be very difficult due to the extreme currents and large amounts of mud brought up with the waves (besides the crocodiles), it remains a popular destination for surfers from all around the world. The Bono is very powerful if there have been heavy rainfalls before, so especially in the rainy season (also check here for more information about the Bono: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kampar_River).

video_title: Powerful Tidal Bore WIPES OUT Docks like a Tsunami! [Watch Until End] | Ganga River, Kolkata
description:
Spectacular moments caught on camera when several meter high waves are speeding up through the Ganga River in India. The 1st wave was so powerful that it destroyed a dock ramp and the 2nd wave at night even washed away some spectators standing too close to the water. In this case a high tide caused such massive waves. Luckily, no serious injuries have been reported in connection with the two incidents.

In the Ganga river, the largest tidal bores usually take place between March and May. Unfortunately every year many people die because they don‚Äôt take the warnings seriously. According to reports a tidal bore in 1876 killed up to a hundred thousand people (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hooghly_River#cite_note-NGeo-7). The power of such tidal waves can be compared to tsunami waves as they wipe out almost everything, including boats, making their way upwards the river.

A tidal bore is a tidal phenomenon in which the incoming tide forms waves of water that travels upwards against the direction of a river or a bay's current. Tidal bores only occur in a few locations worldwide with a large tidal range. Some of the most famous locations for these waves are the Ganges River in Kolkata, India (seen in this video), the Kampar River in Indonesia (can be seen in here: https://youtu.be/pKd0PCI6Sx4) and the Qiantang River in China, at which the world's largest bore is reaching heights of up to 9 meters. Unfortunately several people die each year in connection with these tidal bores (also find more information about a tidal bore here: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tidal_bore).

video_title: My Wild Irish Rose - Full Barbershop song + tag tutorial
description:
My Wild Irish Rose is one the most enduring of close harmony songs. It's sure to be sung wherever barbershop harmonizers gather to sing a few of the old classics. My Wild Irish Rose was one of the many popular songs composed and sung by Chauncey Olcott, who was not only a famous songwriter, but also a Broadway actor and singer of the 1900s and 1910s. The chorus of My Wild Irish Rose is part of the classic Barbershop Polecat songbook that most (if not all) barbershop singers know and love. This particular arrangement is part of the Heritage of Harmony songbook, and features a few variations from the Polecat version, but is mostly similar. The tag (ending) of My Wild Irish Rose is in the pure barbershop tradition. Enjoy, and please sing along!
‚ñ∫ LEARNING TRACKS: http://www.julienneel.com
‚ñ∫ SUPPORT MY ART: http://patreon.com/trudbol
‚ñ∫ DOWNLOAD MP3s: http://trudbol.bandcamp.com
‚ñ∫ FACEBOOK: http://facebook.com/trudbolmusic

--- CREDITS
‚ñ∫ Music & lyrics by Chauncey Olcott (1899)
‚ñ∫ Arranged by SPEQSQSA
‚ñ∫ Performed, recorded & edited by Julien Neel

--- LYRICS
You may sing of your roses which, by other names,
Would smell just as sweetly, they say,
But I know that my Rose would never consent
To have that name taken away.
Her glances are shy when e'er I pass by
The bower, where my true love grows;
And my one wish has been that some day I may win
The heart of my wild Irish Rose
My wild Irish Rose,
The sweetest flow'r that grows,
You may search ev'rywhere,
But none can compare with my wild Irish Rose
My wild Irish Rose,
The dearest flow'r that grows,
And some day for my sake,
She may let me take
The bloom from my wild Irish Rose

#barbershop #irishrose #wildirishrose

video_title: Prayer for Ukraine (–ú–æ–ª–∏—Ç–≤–∞ –∑–∞ –£–∫—Ä–∞—ó–Ω—É) - One-man choir
description:
Prayer for Ukraine (Ukrainian: –ú–æ–ª–∏—Ç–≤–∞ –∑–∞ –£–∫—Ä–∞—ó–Ω—É) is a patriotic Ukrainian hymn published in 1885, which became a spiritual anthem of Ukraine. It gained national significance when it was performed by mass choirs during the Ukrainian War of Independence in 1917‚Äì1920. The hymn was intended to be an official spiritual anthem of Ukraine. It has closed sessions of oblast councils, and has been performed at major national functions. Prayer for Ukraine was performed in Kyiv in 2001 during a parade celebrating the 10th anniversary of Ukraine's independence. It has been part of church services internationally, in response to the 2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine. Oleksandr Konysky wrote a patriotic poem from in 1885 in Kyiv, at a time when the Imperial Russian government suppressed the use of the Ukrainian language. The melody and a choral setting were written by Mykola Lysenko, a composer who inspired a Ukrainian national school of composition.
The version sung here is an original arrangement for male voices, available on my website with audio learning tracks: http://www.julienneel.com
#prayerukraine #prayerforukraine #ukraineanthem

video_title: When Irish Eyes Are Smiling - Barbershop quartet
description:
When Irish Eyes Are Smiling is a tribute song to Ireland that is often sung or played on Saint Patrick's Day (March 17th), during public parades and festivals, where folks wear green attire and shamrocks. Saint Patrick's Day commemorates Saint Patrick, the patron saint of Ireland, and the arrival of Christianity in Ireland, and celebrates the heritage and culture of the Irish in general. The song When Irish Eyes Are Smiling was composed by two Americans, Olcott and Graff Jr, in 1912, at a time where songs in tribute to a romanticised Ireland were very popular both in Britain and the United States.
This is an original a cappella / barbershop arrangement for male voices. I hope you'll enjoy! Happy Saint Patrick's Day!

--- LYRICS
Your smile is a part
Of the love in your heart
It's filled with such laughter and light
There's a tear in your eye
And I'm wondering why
For it never should be there at all
With such pow'r in your smile
Sure a stone you'd beguile
So there's never a teardrop should fall
When your sweet lilting laughter's
Like some fairy song
And your eyes twinkle bright as can be
You should laugh all the while
And all other times smile
And now, smile a smile for me
When Irish eyes are smiling
Sure, 'tis like the morn in Spring
In the lilt of Irish laughter
You can hear the angels sing
When Irish hearts are happy
All the world seems bright and gay
And when Irish eyes are smiling
Sure, they steal your heart away

video_title: Let Me Call You Sweetheart - Valentine's Day Barbershop Quartet
description:
Say Happy Valentine's Day with a song... 1910 barbershop quartet style!
Let Me Call You Sweetheart is a popular song composed a century ago by Leo Friedman and Beth Slater Whitson, and it was a huge hit for the Peerless Quartet in 1911. The catchy melody suggests plenty of harmonizing opportunities that barberhop "woodshedders" (and Kibbers) love ; it's a near guarantee that every barbershop singer has sung the chorus to Let Me Call You Sweetheart at some point! it is often performed as a Singing Valentine by barbershop quartets.

video_title: I'd Love To Live In Loveland - Barbershop quartet
description:
Take a trip in my a cappella time machine! "I'd Love To Live In Loveland" was a popular hit way back in... 1910. This fine close-harmony love song was written by W. R. Williams (Will Rossiter) and is part of the Heritage of Harmony barbershop songbook, which contains many beloved old classics arranged for male voices a cappella. I sang the arrangement 1/2 step lower (in G). The original 1910 sheet can be found here:
https://imslp.org/wiki/I'd_Love_to_Live_in_Loveland_with_a_Girl_Like_You_(Rossiter%2C_Will)

A story of love that is true;
Filled with adventure and glory,
Of wonderful things we can do.
Though we have trouble with Cupid,
Love always finds the way;

It's the sweetest that's told,
So Honey, I just wanna say.

And ev'ry day a holiday with skies of baby blue.
Where roses bloom forever, and sweethearts are always true,

video_title: Thank You For Being a Friend (Golden Girls Theme) - a cappella
description:
Thank You for being a Friend was the theme song of 80s TV series The Golden Girls, which starred Betty White, Bea Arthur, Rue McClanahan, and Estelle Getty. Andrew Gold wrote Thank You For Being a Friend in 1978, and it was covered by Cynthia Fee for the theme song of the television show. Betty White, who recently passed at the age of 99, was an American actress and comedian, and a pioneer of early television, with a career spanning over eight decades! She was the first woman to produce a sitcom (Life with Elizabeth) in the United States, and is often referred to as the "First Lady of Television", a title used for a 2018 documentary detailing her life and career. This cover is my humble tribute to her and this song, in an original 4-part a cappella harmony. All parts sung by me.

--- LYRICS
Thank you for being a friend
Traveled down a road and back again
Your heart is true, you're a pal and a confidant
And if you threw a party
Invited everyone you knew
Well, you would see the biggest gift would be from me
And the card attached would say
Thank you for being a friend

video_title: Mon beau sapin (French "O Christmas Tree") - chant de No√´l a cappella
description:
"Mon beau sapin" is the French version of the traditional German Christmas carol "O Tannenbaum". You may also know it as "O Christmas Tree". Based on a traditional folk song which was unrelated to Christmas, and it became associated with the traditional Christmas tree by the middle of the 19th century and sung as a Christmas carol. I hope you enjoy this cappella arrangement for male quartet in the barbershop style, all voices sung by yours truly. video_title: Michelle (The Beatles) - A cappella cover (barbershop quartet)
description:
Michelle is a Beatles song released in the 1965 album Rubber Soul, recorded at EMI / Abbey Road Studios. The song Michelle was primarily composed by Paul McCartney, with bridge written John Lennon. Michelle was one of McCartney's first compositions and one of his greatest hits. Michelle was a number 1 hit for the Beatles in Belgium, France, Norway, the Netherlands and New Zealand, and it received the Grammy for Song Of The Year in 1967. The French lyrics "Michelle ma belle sont des mots qui vont tr√®s bien ensemble" translates to "Michelle my beauty are words that go together very well".
Here is my original acapella arrangement of this classic, sung in the barbershop quartet style. Hope you enjoy!
If you'd like to support my art, a link to my Patreon page is available below.

video_title: Easy Apple Mini Pies Recipe with 1 Apple and 2 Eggs! No Baking Powder Required!
description:
Hello! Get ready to tantalize your taste buds with this amazing apple pie recipe. This apple pie is a true delight, known for its light and fluffy texture that will leave you craving for more. The best part? It doesn't require any baking powder!

Prepare to be enchanted by the irresistible combination of sweet apples and the warm aroma of cinnamon. As you bite into each slice, the tender apple pieces will melt in your mouth, perfectly complemented by the subtle spice of cinnamon.

2 egg whites
60 grams (1/4 cup) of sugar
2 egg yolks
60 grams (1/2 cup) of all-purpose flour
40 grams (1/4 cup) of Greek yogurt (or sour cream)
7 ml (1/2 tablespoon) of lemon juice
22 ml (1and 1/2 tablespoons) of sunflower oil
1 apple


2 egg whites
60 grams (1/4 cup) of sugar ( 2.12 ounces)
2 egg yolks
60 grams (1/2 cup) of all-purpose flour (2.12 ounces)
40 grams (1/4 cup) of Greek yogurt (or sour cream) (1.41 ounces)
7 ml (1/2 tablespoon) of lemon juice (0.24 ounces)
22 ml (1 1/2 tablespoons) of sunflower oil (0.74 ounces)
1 apple


To create a truly satisfying and irresistible apple pie, follow these steps to bring out the best flavors and textures:

- Start by separating the eggs, using only the egg whites and yolks for different components of the pie. Whisk the egg whites until they form stiff peaks, then gradually add in the sugar, creating a fluffy and sweet meringue-like mixture.

- Next, add the egg yolks and gently stir them into the fluffy mixture. Sift the flour into the bowl and slowly incorporate it with a whisk, ensuring a smooth and well-blended batter.

- In a separate bowl, combine the Greek yogurt (or sour cream), lemon juice, and sunflower oil. Stir until all the ingredients are thoroughly incorporated, resulting in a smooth and creamy batter.

- Now, it's time to assemble the pie. Peel and slice the apple, ensuring thin and uniform slices for even baking.

- Into each pie mold or dish, pour a spoonful of the prepared pie batter, followed by a layer of apple slices sprinkled with cinnamon. Once again, pour the pie batter on top.

- Preheat your oven to 170¬∞C (340¬∞F), and bake the pie for approximately 20-25 minutes. As the pie bakes, your kitchen will be enveloped in the delightful aroma of cinnamon and apples, creating an irresistible anticipation.

Once the pie is golden brown and a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, remove it from the oven and allow it to cool. The cooling process allows the flavors to meld together and ensures that the pie sets properly.

Once completely cooled, you can add a finishing touch by dusting the pie with a light sprinkling of icing sugar. This adds a touch of sweetness and a beautiful presentation to the final product.

With this recipe, you can easily create a delectable apple pie without the need for baking powder. So, gather your ingredients, follow the simple steps, and get ready to savor the irresistible combination of apples, cinnamon, and a whole lot of deliciousness!

video_title: Healthy Chocolate Truffles in 10 Minutes! No-Bake!
description:
Imagine the delight of making these mouthwatering truffles in just ten minutes! Today, i embark on a culinary journey where speed and decadence collide, resulting in an unforgettable treat that will satisfy your chocolate cravings in no time.Lets start!

ingredients:

1 medium banana
30 grams of coconut flour
10 grams of cocoa powder
15 grams of chopped nuts (almonds or walnuts)
1 tablespoon of honey
Additional cocoa powder for rolling

- In a mixing bowl, mash the medium banana until it forms a smooth puree.

- Add the coconut flour, cocoa powder, chopped nuts, and honey to the mashed banana. Mix well until all the ingredients are fully combined and a thick, sticky mixture is formed.

- Take small portions of the mixture and shape them into bite-sized balls using your hands. Repeat this process until all the mixture is used.

- Roll each truffle in the coating of your choice until it is evenly coated. This allows for creativity and variety in the truffle's appearance and flavor. 
(such as cocoa powder, coconut powder, chopped nuts, or even colorful sprinkles)

Serve them as a delightful treat or store them in an airtight container in the refrigerator for later indulgence.

These chocolate banana truffles are a delightful combination of flavors and textures, making them a perfect healthy snack or dessert option. Enjoy the rich, chocolaty goodness with the added nutritional benefits of banana and nuts. Get ready to savor every bite!

video_title: This is the best chocolate cake with nuts you've ever tasted!
description:
In this video, I'll show you how to make the most delicious chocolate cake you've ever tasted, enhanced with the rich and nutty flavor of walnuts. This cake is a perfect balance of chocolate and crunchy nuts, creating a dessert that is both indulgent and satisfying. I'll take you through the step-by-step process of how to make this cake, from preparing the ingredients to baking and decorating the final product. You'll learn tips and tricks for achieving the perfect texture and flavor, so that you can recreate this recipe at home with ease. Whether you're a seasoned baker or just starting out, this chocolate cake with walnuts is sure to impress your friends and family. So join me in the kitchen and let's get started!

Ingredients:
130 ml of hot milk (1/2 cup + 2 tablespoons) (4.4 oz)
50 grams of sugar (1/4 cup) (1.8 oz)
20 grams of cocoa powder (1/4 cup) (0.7 oz)
2 eggs
80 grams of sugar (1/3 cup) (2.8 oz)
80 ml of sunflower oil (1/3 cup) (2.7 oz)
130 grams of all-purpose flour (1 cup + 1 tablespoon) (4.6 oz)
3 grams of baking powder (1/2 teaspoon) (0.1 oz)
40 grams of chopped walnuts (1/3 cup) (1.4 oz)

Heavy cream (40 g) (3 tablespoons) (1.4 oz)
Dark chocolate (60 g) (1/3 cup) (2.1 oz)


-If you're a fan of chocolate cake and nuts, then you're in for a treat! In this recipe, we'll be making a delicious chocolate cake with walnuts that is sure to satisfy your sweet tooth. 
To start, we'll need to heat up 130 ml of milk until it's hot, then add 50 grams of sugar and 20 grams of cocoa powder, stirring the mixture until it's smooth. In a separate bowl, we'll stir together 2 eggs and 80 grams of sugar for 3-4 minutes until the mixture becomes creamy, then add in 80 ml of sunflower oil and the milk mixture, whisking everything together until it's well combined.

Next, we'll add in 130 grams of all-purpose flour and 3 grams of baking powder, folding the dry ingredients into the wet mixture until there are no lumps. Finally, we'll add in 40 grams of chopped walnuts and mix everything together one last time.

Pour the batter into a cake pan (20 x 10 x 8 cm) and bake for 35-40 minutes at 180¬∞C in a preheated oven. Once the cake is done, let it cool down to room temperature while we prepare the topping.

For the topping, we'll need 40 grams of heavy cream and 60 grams of dark chocolate. Heat them up in the microwave for 30 seconds, then mix them together until they're smooth. Pour the chocolate ganache over the cooled cake and spread it evenly using a spatula or a knife.You can sprinkle some chopped walnuts or your favorite nuts on top for extra crunch and flavor.

Now all that's left to do is slice into the cake and enjoy! This recipe is perfect for sharing with friends and family, or for satisfying your own sweet cravings.

Note: If you prefer a different type of nut, such as almonds or peanuts, you can also mix them into the cake batter instead of using walnuts. This recipe is versatile and can be customized to your liking.

video_title: Easy Homemade Cake Just Like Your Grandma Used To Make!
description:
Welcome to my channel, cake lovers! Today, I'm excited to share with you a simple and nostalgic cake recipe that will take you back to your childhood. This recipe requires only basic ingredients that you probably already have in your pantry, and the best part is that there's no need for fancy equipment or electric mixers. Just a bit of manual mixing and some love are all you need to create this delicious and satisfying cake. In this video, I'll guide you through every step of the process, from mixing the batter to baking it to perfection. So put on your apron, grab a whisk, and let's get started on this wonderful baking adventure together!


Ingredients
2 eggs
130 grams of sugar (1/2 cup + 2 tablespoons)
1/2 tsp vanilla
150 ml of milk (2/3 cup)
70 ml of sunflower oil (5 tablespoons)
200 grams of all-purpose flour (1 and 2/3 cups)
7 grams of baking powder (1 and 3/4 teaspoons)



2 eggs
130 grams (4.6 ounces) of sugar
1/2 tsp vanilla
150 ml (5.1 ounces) of milk
70 ml (2.4 ounces) of sunflower oil
200 grams (7.1 ounces) of all-purpose flour
7 grams (0.25 ounces) of baking powder


Preheat your oven to 180¬∞C (350¬∞F).
- Grease or line an 18cm (7 inch) cake pan with parchment paper.
- In a large bowl, beat the eggs with the sugar and vanilla using a whisk or electric mixer until the mixture is light and creamy.
- Pour the milk and sunflower oil into the bowl, and mix well.
- Sift the flour and baking powder into the bowl, and mix until just combined. Be careful not to overmix the batter.
- Pour the batter into the prepared cake pan and tap it a few times to release any air bubbles.
- Bake for 40-50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean.
- Let the cake cool in the pan for 10 minutes, then turn it out onto a wire rack to cool completely.
Cut the cake into pieces and serve on its own, or with your favorite frosting or topping.
Enjoy your simple and nostalgic cake!

video_title: Easy Nutella-Stuffed Buns Recipe Anyone Can Make!
description:
Hello everyone! Welcome back to my channel. Today, I'm excited to share with you my recipe for easy and delicious Nutella-stuffed buns. These buns are a perfect treat for breakfast or snack time, and they're sure to satisfy any sweet tooth.

In this video, I'll show you step-by-step how to make these buns from scratch using simple ingredients like flour, sugar, and milk. We'll start by making the dough, then move on to shaping and filling the buns with rich and creamy Nutella chocolate spread. Finally, we'll bake them to golden perfection.

Whether you're an experienced baker or a beginner in the kitchen, this Nutella-stuffed buns recipe is easy to follow and sure to impress. 

If you enjoy this video, please consider supporting my channel by liking, commenting, and subscribing. Your support means the world to me and helps me create more content like this. So, let's get started!


Ingredients:
1 egg 
40 grams of sugar (3 tablespoons)
Sunflower oil 40 ml (3 tablespoons)
1 pinch of salt
120 ml milk (40-45 ¬∞C) (1/2 cup)
1 tablespoon of instant dry yeast (4 grams)
300 grams of all-purpose flour (2, 1/2 cups)

1 egg
1.4 oz of sugar
1.4 oz of sunflower oil
1 pinch of salt
4.05 fl oz of milk (40-45¬∞C)
0.14 oz of instant dry yeast (1 tablespoon)
10.58 oz of all-purpose flour

1. In a bowl, mix 1 egg, 40 grams (1/4 cup) of sugar, 40 ml (3 tablespoons) of sunflower oil, a pinch of salt, 120 ml (1/2 cup) of milk at 40-45 ¬∞C (105-115 ¬∞F), and 1 tablespoon of instant dry yeast (4 grams).
2. Add the flour gradually while mixing until the dough comes together
3.Knead the dough on a floured surface for 10 minutes until it becomes smooth and elastic.
4. Place the dough in a clean bowl, cover it with a towel, and let it rest for 1-1.5 hours in a warm place until it doubles in size.
5. Divide the dough into 6 to 8 equal parts.
6.Open each ball of dough with your hands and fill with Nutella chocolate.
7. Tie the dough tightly so that the chocolate does not fall out during baking.
8. Place the buns on a baking tray lined with parchment paper, cover them with a towel, and let them rest for another 20 minutes.
9.Preheat the oven to 180¬∞C.
10. Mix together 1 egg yolk and 1 tablespoon of milk and brush it over the buns.
11. Bake for 20-25 minutes in the preheated oven until they turn golden brown.
12. Let them cool on a wire rack.
13. Sprinkle with icing sugar before serving.
Enjoy your delicious Nutella-filled chocolate buns!

video_title: Bake a Moist and Easy Chocolate Chip Cake with Just a Few Basic Ingredients!
description:
Looking for a delicious, easy-to-make cake that's guaranteed to impress? Look no further than this Amazing Chocolate Chip Cake! With its moist texture and perfect balance of sweet vanilla and rich chocolate chips, this cake is sure to become a new favorite in your recipe collection.

To make this cake, you'll need just a handful of simple ingredients, including eggs, sugar, plain yogurt, vanilla extract, all-purpose flour, baking powder, salt, and of course, plenty of chocolate chips. The batter comes together quickly and easily, and bakes up perfectly in just 40-45 minutes in a preheated oven.

Whether you're looking for a crowd-pleasing dessert for a special occasion or simply want to treat yourself to a slice of something sweet and delicious, this Amazing Chocolate Chip Cake is sure to hit the spot. So why wait? Get baking today and discover your new favorite cake recipe!

**Turn on cc (subtitle)**

‚ô° Please subscribe, share and comment.

‚ñ∂Ingredients
2 eggs (at room temperature)
55 grams (1/4 cup) of sugar
80 grams (1/3 cup) of plain yogurt
80 ml ( 1/3 cup) of sunflower oil
1/2 teaspoon of vanilla extract
135g (1 cup + 1 tablespoon) all-purpose flour
1 teaspoon baking powder
A pinch of salt
70 grams (1/2 cup) of chocolate chips

Cake pan size: 8 x 4 x 3 inches (20 x 10 x 8 cm)

Bake for 40-45 minutes at 350¬∞F (180¬∞C) in a preheated oven.

‚ñ∂Ingredients

2 eggs (room temperature)
1.94 oz (1/4 cup) sugar
2.82 oz (1/3 cup) plain yogurt 
2.7 fluid oz (1/3 cup) sunflower oil
0.17 oz (1/2 tsp) vanilla extract
4.76 oz (1 cup + 1 tbsp) all-purpose flour
0.18 oz (1 tsp) baking powder
1 pinch of salt
2.47 oz (1/2 cup) chocolate chips

Cake pan size: 8 x 4 x 3 inches (20 x 10 x 8 cm)

Bake for 40-45 minutes at 350¬∞F in a preheated oven
...............................................
1. Preheat your oven to 350¬∞F (180¬∞C).
2. In a mixing bowl, crack in 2 eggs (at room temperature).
3. Add 55 grams (1/4 cup) of sugar to the eggs and beat with an electric mixer on medium-high speed until the mixture is thick, pale and doubled in volume.
4. Add 80 grams (1/3 cup) of plain yogurt, 80 ml of oil, and 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla extract to the mixing bowl and mix on low speed for another minute until well combined.
5. Sift in 135g (1 cup + 1 tablespoon) all-purpose flour, 1 teaspoon baking powder, and a pinch of salt.
Stir gently until smooth. (You can stir for 30 seconds at low speed)
6. Add 70 grams (1/2 cup) of chocolate chips and mix with a whisk.
7. Pour the batter into a greased 3 x 4 x 8 inch cake pan (8 x 10 x 20 cm) and smooth the surface with a spatula.
Bake the cake in the preheated oven for 40-45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Let the cake cool in the pan for 5-10 minutes, then transfer it to a wire rack to cool completely.

video_title: Easily make a moist and fluffy chocolate cake with this recipe!
description:
In this video, we'll show you how to make a delicious and moist chocolate cake that's perfect for any occasion. With just a few simple ingredients and easy-to-follow steps, you can create a cake that will impress your friends and family.

The result is a moist and fluffy chocolate cake that's rich and chocolaty, with a tender crumb that melts in your mouth. You can serve it on its own, dusted with powdered sugar, or with a dollop of whipped cream or your favorite frosting. Get creative and decorate it with fresh berries, chocolate shavings, or edible flowers.

So grab your apron and let's get baking!üòä


Ingredients:

1 1/3 cups (170 grams) all-purpose flour
1/3 cup (40 grams) cocoa powder
1 teaspoon (3 grams) baking powder
1 teaspoon (3 grams) baking soda
2 eggs (room temperature)
2/3 cup (130 grams) granulated sugar
1/3 cup (70 ml) vegetable oil
1/2 cup (130 ml) boiling water
.............................................................

1 1/3 cups (6.8 ounces) all-purpose flour
1/3 cup (1.4 ounces) cocoa powder
1 teaspoon (0.1 ounces) baking powder
1 teaspoon (0.1 ounces) baking soda
2 large eggs (room temperature)
2/3 cup (4.6 ounces) granulated sugar
1/3 cup (2.4 fluid ounces) vegetable oil
1/2 cup (4.4 fluid ounces) boiling water


1.Heat the oven to 180¬∞C and grease an 18 cm cake pan with butter or cooking spray (or baking paper).
2. In a medium bowl, mix all purpose flour, cocoa powder, baking powder and baking soda and set aside.
3. In a separate bowl, beat the eggs and granulated sugar until they are completely combined and the color becomes light.
4. Add vegetable oil to the egg mixture and mix until smooth.
5. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet mixture while mixing on low speed until just combined.
6. Add boiling water and stir the dough until smooth.
7. Pour the batter into the prepared cake mold.
8. Bake for 40-50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean.
9. Remove the cake from the oven and place it in the mold for 10 minutes to cool.
10. After 10 minutes, transfer the cake to a wire rack to cool completely.

Serve the cake with whipped cream, frosting or any topping of your choice.

This chocolate cake is suitable for any occasion and is easy to make with simple ingredients. Enjoy the rich chocolate flavor and moist texture of this delicious dessert!

video_title: Delicious Orange Cookie Sticks for Dipping in Hot Drinks!
description:
Welcome to this recipe for Delicious Orange Cookie Sticks for Dipping in Hot Drinks! If you're looking for a sweet treat to enjoy with your favorite hot beverage, these fragrant and buttery cookie sticks are the perfect choice. With the bright and citrusy flavor of orange zest and juice, these cookies are sure to awaken your taste buds and make your hot drink experience even more enjoyable.

Not only are these cookies delicious, but they're also easy to make. The dough comes together quickly and is ready to roll out and shape into cookie sticks in no time. And once they're baked to a light golden brown, you can dip them into your hot drink of choice for a sweet and satisfying snack.

So why not give this recipe a try? Whether you're a fan of coffee, tea, or hot chocolate, these Delicious Orange Cookie Sticks for Dipping in Hot Drinks are sure to be a hit!

‚ñ∂Ingredients
The zest of one orange
1/4 cup (50g / 1.8 oz) sugar
1/2 tsp vanilla extract
1/4 cup (65g / 2.3 oz) unsalted butter (softened)
1 cup (130g / 4.6 oz) all-purpose flour
1/4 cup (30g / 1 oz) cornstarch
A pinch of salt
1 1/2 tbsp (20ml / 0.7 oz) freshly squeezed orange juice


- To start, you'll need to zest one orange and mix the zest into 50g of sugar. Rubbing the zest into the sugar with your fingertips beforehand helps to release the essential oils and make the cookies even more fragrant.

- Then add 1/2 tsp of vanilla extract and 65g of softened unsalted butter, and mix until light and fluffy.
- Sift in 130g of all-purpose flour, 30g of cornstarch, and a pinch of salt, and stir until the dough comes together. Add 20ml of freshly squeezed orange juice and mix until the dough forms a ball.

- Roll out the dough to a thickness of about 1cm between two sheets of baking paper. Cut the dough into cookie sticks that are about 12cm long, 1cm wide, and 1cm thick, and place them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.

- Bake the cookies for 15-18 minutes at 180¬∞C in a preheated oven until they turn a light golden brown. Once they're done, take them out of the oven and let them cool on the baking sheet for a few minutes before transferring them to a wire rack to cool completely.

You can also drizzle or dip the cookie sticks in melted dark chocolate or milk chocolate for an extra special treat. And there you have it, delicious and fragrant orange shortbread cookie sticks that are perfect for dipping in your favorite hot beverage. Enjoy!

video_title: The best orange crinkle cookies you've ever tasted!
description:
Get ready for a taste sensation with these incredible orange crinkle cookies! These cookies are moist, buttery, and delicate, with a fragrant orange flavor that will make your taste buds sing. They're so delicious, you won't be able to stop at just one!
These are the best orange crinkle cookies you've ever tasted, and you won't believe how simple they are to make!


‚ñ∂Ingredients
75g sugar = 2.65 oz = 1/3 cup
Zest of 1 orange
1 medium egg (room temperature)
1/2 tsp vanilla
35g unsalted butter (melted and cooled to room temperature) = 1.23 oz = 2 1/2 tablespoons
1 tbsp orange juice
125g all-purpose flour = 4.41 oz = 1 cup
1/2 tsp baking powder
1 pinch of salt

- To begin, mix 75g of sugar with the zest of 1 orange, using your fingertips to rub the orange zest into the sugar. This will help release the essential oils from the orange zest and make the cookies more fragrant. Then, add 1 medium room temperature egg, 1/2 tsp of vanilla, 35g of melted and cooled unsalted butter, and 1 tbsp of orange juice to the sugar and orange zest mixture.

- Next, add 125g of all-purpose flour, 1/2 tsp of baking powder, and a pinch of salt to the mixture and mix until everything is well combined. After that, put the dough in the refrigerator for 2 hours to chill.

- When the dough has chilled, preheat your oven to 180¬∞C and prepare an oven tray. Roll the dough into small balls, then roll them in sugar and then in powdered sugar. Finally, roll the balls again in your hands to coat them evenly and put them on the oven tray. You can also sprinkle some powdered sugar on the cookies.

Bake the cookies for 10-12 minutes in the preheated oven. After baking, let the cookies cool completely before serving.
These orange crinkle cookies are perfect for any occasion and are sure to be a hit with anyone who loves the taste of citrus. Don't forget to subscribe, share, and comment if you enjoy this recipe!
